%N A238343 Triangle T(n,k) read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of compositions of n with k descents, n>=0, 0<=k<=n.
%C A238343 Counting ascents gives the same triangle.
%C A238343 For n > 0, also the number of compositions of n with k + 1 maximal weakly increasing runs. - _Gus Wiseman_, Mar 23 2020
%D A238343 S. Heubach and T. Mansour, Combinatorics of Compositions and Words, CRC Press, 2010. (See Section 4.2)
%H A238343 Joerg Arndt and Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A238343/b238343.txt">Rows n = 0..140, flattened</a>
%H A238343 Eder G. Santos, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.20253">Distributions of Inversions and Descents over Integer Compositions</a>, arXiv:2605.20253 [math.GM], 2026.
%F A238343 Sum_{k=0..n} k * T(n,k) = A045883(n-2) for n>=2.
%F A238343 G.f.: Sum_{k>=0} x^k/((1-x)(1-x^2)...(1-x^k)) * A_k(x,y), where A_k(x,y) is the joint distribution of inversion number and descent number statistics over permutations of {1,2,...,k}, also known as the q-Eulerian polynomial. - _Eder G. Santos_, May 21 2026
